Topic: HTML Fundamentals

Practical - Hands-on HTML Structure and Basic Tags with Attributes

Objective:
The objective of this experiment is to develop an advanced HTML5 webpage that demonstrates the use of various HTML5 elements and attributes to create a well-structured, accessible, and responsive web page. The webpage includes semantic elements such as <header>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <footer>, and <nav> to enhance the document's structure and readability. It incorporates multimedia elements by embedding images with <figure> and <figcaption> tags and integrating a YouTube video using the <iframe> element. Accessibility is improved through the use of aria-label attributes for better navigation and form elements with appropriate label tags and required attributes to ensure a user-friendly experience. The design is made responsive by linking an external CSS stylesheet, ensuring the page looks appealing across various devices. Additionally, a JavaScript file is included to add interactivity and enhance user experience. A contact form is provided to demonstrate form handling in HTML5, capturing user information and submitting it via a POST request. Metadata is included to improve SEO and browser compatibility. By achieving these objectives, the experiment aims to serve as a comprehensive example of advanced HTML5 techniques and modern web development practices.

Problem Statement:Implementing basic on HTML Structure and Basic Tags with Attributes

Procedure:

<!DOCTYPE html> 
 <html lang="en"> 
 <head> 
    <meta charset="UTF-8"> 
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"> 
    <meta name="description" content="An advanced HTML5 example demonstrating         	various elements and attributes"> 
    <title>Advanced HTML5 Example</title> 
    <style>
        /* CSS Styling */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        header {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 1rem 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
      
       nav ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }
        nav ul li {
            display: inline;
            margin: 0 10px;
        }
        nav ul li a {
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        main {
            padding: 20px;
        }
        section {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        figure {
            text-align: center;
        }
        figcaption {
            font-style: italic;
        }
        form {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        form fieldset {
            border: none;
        }
        form label, form input, form textarea, form button {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        footer {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            width: 100%;
        }
    </style>
</head> 
 

<body> 
<!-- Header Section --> 
    <header> 
        <nav> 
            <ul> 
                <li><a href="#home" aria-label="Home">Home</a></li> 
                <li><a href="#about" aria-label="About">About</a></li> 
                <li><a href="#services" aria-label="Services">Services</a></li> 
                <li><a href="#contact" aria-label="Contact">Contact</a></li> 
            </ul> 
        </nav> 
    </header> 
 
<!-- Main Content --> 
    <main> 
        <section id="home"> 
            <h1>Welcome to Our Advanced HTML5 Page</h1> 
            <p>This page demonstrates various HTML5 elements and attributes at an    	advanced level.</p> 
            <figure> 
                <img src="images/advanced-example.jpg" alt="Advanced HTML5 Example 		Image" width="600" height="400"> 
                <figcaption>Advanced HTML5 Example</figcaption> 
            </figure> 
        </section> 
 
    <section id="about"> 
            <h2>About Us</h2> 
            <p>We specialize in modern web development techniques and provide
            comprehensive tutorials for all levels.</p> 
        </section>
        <section id="services"> 
            <h2>Our Services</h2> 
            <article> 
                <h3>Web Development</h3> 
                <p>We build responsive and accessible web applications using the latest web 		technologies.</p> 
            </article> 
            <article> 
                <h3>SEO Optimization</h3> 
                <p>Our SEO services help improve your website's visibility and ranking on 		search engines.</p> 
            </article> 
        </section> 
        <section id="contact"> 
            <h2>Contact Us</h2> 
            <form action="/submit-form" method="POST"> 
                <fieldset> 
                    <legend>Contact Information</legend> 
                    <label for="name">Name:</label> 
                    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required> 
                    <label for="email">Email:</label> 
                    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required> 
                    <label for="message">Message:</label> 
                    <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" required></textarea> 
                    <button type="submit">Submit</button> 
                </fieldset> 
            </form> 
        </section> 
    </main> 
<!-- Footer Section --> 
    <footer> 
        <address> 
            <p>Contact us at <a href="mailto:info@example.com">info@example.com</a>	</p> 
        </address> 
        <p>&copy; 2024 Advanced HTML5 Example. All rights reserved.</p> 
    </footer> 
<!-- Embedded YouTube Video --> 
    <section id="video"> 
        <h2>Watch Our Introduction Video</h2> 
        <iframe width="560" 
height="315"  
src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID" frameborder="0"
 allowfullscreen> 
        </iframe> 
    </section>   
<!-- JavaScript --> 
    <script>
        // JavaScript
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const form = document.querySelector('form');
            form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
                e.preventDefault();
                const name = document.getElementById('name').value;
                const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
                const message = document.getElementById('message').value;
                alert(`Name: ${name}\nEmail: ${email}\nMessage: ${message}`);
            });
        });
    </script> 
</body> 
</html>
